<T>__{the grand staircase:}
<A>__{the german captain marches up the stairs purposefully, as if he's on urgent business.}
<L>__{interior loft and attic day}
<A>__{the german captain enters. he puts two fingers in his mouth and whistles.}
<C>__{the german captain}
<D>__{open up.}
<A>__{after a moment, the trapdoor shifts and szpilman looks down. the german captain takes a package from his shoulder bag and throws it up into the loft. he turns to go.}
<C>__{szpilman}
<D>__{please.}
<A>__{the german captain stops.}
<C>__{szpilman}
<D>__{what's all that gunfire?}
<C>__{the german captain}
<D>__{the russians. on the other side of the river.}
<P>__{(turns to leave,}
<D>__{stops; with a touch}
<P>__{of irony:)}
<D>__{all you have to do is hang on for a few more weeks.}
<A>__{he goes quickly. szpilman opens the package, finds bread and marmalade. then he finds a tin opener.}
